  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed dwelling would, by reason of its single storey built form, cramped nature on an uncharacteristically small plot and its close proximity to the shared boundaries either side of the site, appear as a visually intrusive feature in the streetscene that would be harmful to the established local pattern of development along Abbotts Close. It would also give rise to garden sizes which are materially out of keeping with that prevailing in the locality, resulting in an intrusive form of development when seen from the rear garden environment of Mawney Road. It would therefore be harmful to the character and appearance of the surrounding area contrary to Local Plan Policies 7 and 26.",
    "In the event that this application is allowed through the appeals process, the proposals would be liable for the following CIL contributions:",
